        <bioghist id="ref35">
            <head>Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Curt Royston is best known for his proficiency in a variety of media: painting, sculpture, photography, film, and video, and often in combination. His work has been shown extensively throughout the United States and Europe including a 1987 one-man exhibition at the Whitney Museum of American Art.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <arrangement id="ref36">
            <head>Arrangement</head>
            <p>This collection is arranged into four series by format.</p>
            <list numeration="arabic" type="ordered">
                <item>Series I: Reviews</item>
                <item>Series II: Transparencies</item>
                <item>Series III: Film</item>
                <item>Series IV: Video</item>
            </list>
        </arrangement>
        <scopecontent id="ref37">
            <head>Scope and Content</head>
            <p>This collection contains reviews, promotional matierals, transparencies, film and video relating to Curt Royston's career as a filmmaker.</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <prefercite id="ref38">
            <head>Preferred Citation</head>
